fields.body: I didn't do it with a Leica but I did dig out the Pentax K1000 I bought used when I went to college twenty years ago and haven't used for years. I bought a 50mm f/1.7 lens on eBay and have been using nothing but this (aside from some casual phone/point-and-shoot shots occasionally), with Tri-X, for over a year now.
fields.title: The Online Photographer: 'A Leica for a Year' a Year Later
fields.body_more_html: I've really enjoyed it and it's been a real refresher -- I was only using a digital point-and-shoot before, not wanting the bulk and expense of a digital SLR. But I didn't like the pictures it took and wasn't sure what to do next. So black and white film on my old SLR was just the change I was after.
